column1: #Text=You 're forced to choose between having either India or China blown off the face of the Earth , and if you do n't choose , they both go .
#Text=They are equal in population according to the 2000 census in each country , with each having roughly 1.2 billion people .
#Text=You would choose India because your grandparents are from China !
#Text=No , to me , India is a democracy , it 's the world 's largest democracy and I 've been there .
#Text=I found it be a really spiritual place .
#Text=Some of the most intelligent people I have ever met are from India .
#Text=And China , I have to say , not so much .
#Text=I have only been to the countryside .
#Text=My grandfather is Chinese as well ; I 'm a quarter Chinese .
#Text=I just think they are more barbaric by their culture ... .
#Text=We 're never going to tour China now ... .
#Text=You would go with China too , then ?
#Text=Well , I mean , I do n't know , come on ...

#Text=I actually knew a guy , he lost a bet and he had to have breasts for a year .
#Text=And actually his breasts were pretty nice .

#Text=When I was in college I had a couple of friends who were rave kids -- they also went to my college -- and the guy walked around with very large breasts , and our friend Koo would follow him on the street and after he passed people who noticed his large breasts

#Text=It was surprising , because the people who looked the most uptight generally responded with things like , " Yeah , sure , he does n't seem so bad . "
